Police said the death is not being treated as suspicious.

Shoppers and motorists were warned to expect disruption.

Joe Cole said on Twitter: 'It's all going on in Farnborough this morning, police everywhere.'

The dead pensioner has not been named by police but his next of kin have been informed.

A post mortem examination is expected to take place as well as an inquest.

A spokesman for Hampshire Police said: 'Police were called at 8.20am, to reports of a man jumping from the roof.

'Despite emergency medical treatment at the scene, the man, aged 84 and local to the area, died of his injuries.

'Next-of-kin have been informed.

'The death is not being treated as suspicious, and a file is being prepared for the coroner.'

